================================================================================
  MAIL ANALYZER AGENT — COMPLETE ENDPOINT REFERENCE
================================================================================

Base URL (local)  : http://127.0.0.1:8000
Base URL (public) : https://<your-ngrok-url>   (set in WEBHOOK_PUBLIC_URL)

All responses are JSON unless otherwise stated.
The agent is fully autonomous — real emails trigger it automatically via
Gmail Pub/Sub. Use POST /test/simulate to trigger the pipeline manually.

================================================================================
  ENDPOINT INDEX
================================================================================

  1.  GET  /                    Serve live monitoring dashboard (HTML)
  2.  GET  /health              Liveness check
  3.  GET  /status              Full configuration diagnostic
  4.  GET  /events              Server-Sent Events live stream
  5.  POST /webhook/gmail       Gmail Pub/Sub push notification (auto-trigger)
  6.  POST /test/simulate       Manually inject a test email into the pipeline

================================================================================
  1. GET /
================================================================================

Description:
  Serves the live monitoring dashboard (dashboard/index.html).
  Open this in a browser to watch emails being processed in real time.

URL:
  GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/

Response:
  Status  : 200 OK
  Content-Type : text/html; charset=utf-8
  Body    : Full HTML page (dashboard/index.html)

  On missing dashboard file:
  Status  : 404 Not Found
  Body    : <h1>Dashboard not found</h1>

Example (browser):
  Open: http://127.0.0.1:8000/

================================================================================
  2. GET /health
================================================================================

Description:
  Lightweight liveness check. Returns server status, the configured
  Pub/Sub push endpoint URL, number of connected SSE clients, and the
  last processed historyId.

URL:
  GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/health

Response:
  Status  : 200 OK
  Content-Type : application/json

  Body:
  {
    "status": "ok",
    "webhook_url": "https://<ngrok-url>/webhook/gmail",
    "connected_clients": 1,
    "last_history_id": "12345"
  }

  Field descriptions:
  ┌─────────────────────┬──────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Field               │ Type     │ Description                             │
  ├─────────────────────┼──────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ status              │ string   │ Always "ok" if server is running        │
  │ webhook_url         │ string   │ The URL Google pushes Pub/Sub events to │
  │ connected_clients   │ integer  │ Number of active SSE dashboard clients  │
  │ last_history_id     │ string   │ Last Gmail historyId received, or "none"│
  └─────────────────────┴──────────┴─────────────────────────────────────────┘

Example (curl):
  curl http://127.0.0.1:8000/health

================================================================================
  3. GET /status
================================================================================

Description:
  Full configuration diagnostic. Shows every config value, whether
  required files exist, and a list of issues preventing the agent from
  working. Use this to debug setup problems.

URL:
  GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/status

Response:
  Status  : 200 OK
  Content-Type : application/json

  Body (healthy):
  {
    "status": "ready",
    "config": {
      "gmail_address": "your-inbox@gmail.com",
      "pubsub_topic": "projects/your-project-id/topics/your-topic-name",
      "gcp_project_id": "your-project-id",
      "webhook_url": "https://<ngrok-url>/webhook/gmail",
      "credentials_exists": true,
      "token_exists": true,
      "sse_clients": 1,
      "processed_messages": 12
    },
    "issues": []
  }

  Body (misconfigured):
  {
    "status": "misconfigured",
    "config": {
      "gmail_address": "",
      "pubsub_topic": "",
      "gcp_project_id": "your-project-id",
      "webhook_url": "/webhook/gmail",
      "credentials_exists": false,
      "token_exists": false,
      "sse_clients": 0,
      "processed_messages": 0
    },
    "issues": [
      "GMAIL_ADDRESS not set in .env",
      "PUBSUB_TOPIC not set in .env",
      "GCP_PROJECT_ID not set in .env",
      "WEBHOOK_PUBLIC_URL not set in .env",
      "credentials.json not found in secrets/",
      "token.json missing — run: python -m src.services.gmail.watcher"
    ]
  }

  Field descriptions:
  ┌──────────────────────┬─────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Field                │ Type    │ Description                              │
  ├──────────────────────┼─────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ status               │ string  │ "ready" or "misconfigured"               │
  │ config.gmail_address │ string  │ Monitored Gmail inbox address            │
  │ config.pubsub_topic  │ string  │ Google Cloud Pub/Sub topic name          │
  │ config.gcp_project_id│ string  │ Google Cloud project ID                  │
  │ config.webhook_url   │ string  │ Public push endpoint for Pub/Sub         │
  │ config.credentials_  │ boolean │ Whether credentials.json exists in       │
  │       exists         │         │ secrets/                                 │
  │ config.token_exists  │ boolean │ Whether token.json exists in secrets/    │
  │ config.sse_clients   │ integer │ Active SSE connections                   │
  │ config.processed_    │ integer │ Total messages processed since startup   │
  │       messages       │         │                                          │
  │ issues               │ array   │ List of config problems found (empty=[]) │
  └──────────────────────┴─────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────┘

Example (curl):
  curl http://127.0.0.1:8000/status

================================================================================
  4. GET /events
================================================================================

Description:
  Server-Sent Events (SSE) stream. The dashboard connects here to receive
  live updates as emails are processed. Each event is a JSON object on a
  single "data:" line. Can also be consumed by any SSE-capable client.

URL:
  GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/events

Request:
  Headers : Accept: text/event-stream   (optional but recommended)

Response:
  Status       : 200 OK
  Content-Type : text/event-stream
  Cache-Control: no-cache
  Connection   : keep-alive (long-lived stream)

  Every event line format:
    data: <JSON object>\n\n

  Heartbeat (every 20s to keep connection alive):
    : heartbeat\n\n

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Event Types
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  All events share this outer envelope:
  {
    "type": "<event_type>",
    "timestamp": "2026-01-15T11:19:55.255Z",
    "data": { ... }
  }

  ── Event: connected ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Fired immediately after the SSE connection is established.

  {
    "type": "connected",
    "timestamp": "2026-01-15T11:19:55.255Z",
    "data": {}
  }

  ── Event: processing_started ────────────────────────────────────────────
  Fired when a new message ID is picked up and about to be fetched.

  {
    "type": "processing_started",
    "timestamp": "2026-01-15T11:19:55.255Z",
    "data": {
      "message_id": "1a2b3c4d5e6f7890"
    }
  }

  ── Event: email_fetched ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Fired after the full email is retrieved from the Gmail API.

  {
    "type": "email_fetched",
    "timestamp": "2026-01-15T11:19:56.100Z",
    "data": {
      "message_id": "1a2b3c4d5e6f7890",
      "subject": "Meeting tomorrow at 10am",
      "sender": "John Smith <john.smith@example.com>"
    }
  }

  ── Event: analysis_complete ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  Fired when the supervisor agent has finished all tool calls and the
  final report is ready. This is the main output event.

  {
    "type": "analysis_complete",
    "timestamp": "2026-01-15T11:20:44.000Z",
    "data": {
      <full report object — see Full Report Schema section below>
    }
  }

  ── Event: processing_error ──────────────────────────────────────────────
  Fired if the pipeline fails for a message.

  {
    "type": "processing_error",
    "timestamp": "2026-01-15T11:20:44.000Z",
    "data": {
      "message_id": "1a2b3c4d5e6f7890",
      "error": "Failed to fetch email: connection timeout"
    }
  }

Example (JavaScript):
  const es = new EventSource('http://127.0.0.1:8000/events');
  es.onmessage = (e) => {
    const event = JSON.parse(e.data);
    if (event.type === 'analysis_complete') {
      console.log(event.data.decision.recommendation);
    }
  };

Example (curl):
  curl -N http://127.0.0.1:8000/events

================================================================================
  5. POST /webhook/gmail
================================================================================

Description:
  Receives Gmail Pub/Sub push notifications from Google Cloud.
  This endpoint is called AUTOMATICALLY by Google — you never call it
  manually. Google calls it every time a new email arrives in the
  monitored Gmail inbox.

  Requirements:
  - Must be publicly reachable via HTTPS (use ngrok in development)
  - Must respond within 10 seconds or Google retries the delivery
  - Must return HTTP 200 to acknowledge receipt

URL:
  POST https://<your-ngrok-url>/webhook/gmail
  (or http://127.0.0.1:8000/webhook/gmail for local testing)

Request:
  Method       : POST
  Content-Type : application/json
  Body         : Google Cloud Pub/Sub push message format

  {
    "message": {
      "data": "<base64url-encoded JSON string>",
      "messageId": "12345678901234567",
      "message_id": "12345678901234567",
      "publishTime": "2026-01-15T10:34:29.535Z",
      "publish_time": "2026-01-15T10:34:29.535Z"
    },
    "subscription": "projects/your-project-id/subscriptions/your-subscription-name"
  }

  The "data" field base64-decodes to:
  {
    "emailAddress": "your-inbox@gmail.com",
    "historyId": "12345"
  }

  Field descriptions:
  ┌──────────────────────┬────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Field                │ Type   │ Description                              │
  ├──────────────────────┼────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ message.data         │ string │ Base64url-encoded notification payload   │
  │ message.messageId    │ string │ Pub/Sub message ID (not Gmail message ID)│
  │ message.publishTime  │ string │ ISO 8601 timestamp from Google           │
  │ subscription         │ string │ Full Pub/Sub subscription resource name  │
  │ data.emailAddress    │ string │ The monitored Gmail address              │
  │ data.historyId       │ string │ Gmail history ID — used to fetch new msgs│
  └──────────────────────┴────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────┘

Response:
  Status  : 200 OK
  Body    : (empty)

  If invalid JSON:
  Status  : 204 No Content

  If data field is empty or undecodable:
  Status  : 204 No Content

  NOTE: HTTP 204 tells Google "received but nothing to do".
        HTTP 200 tells Google "received and processing".
        Any non-2xx response causes Google to retry delivery.

Processing (after responding 200):
  All processing happens in a background thread:
  1. Calls Gmail History API (startHistoryId = previous historyId)
  2. For each new message ID found → fetch full email → run supervisor agent
  3. If history returns nothing → fallback: fetch latest inbox message
  4. Results broadcast to all SSE clients via /events

================================================================================
  6. POST /test/simulate
================================================================================

Description:
  Injects a pre-built fake phishing email directly into the supervisor
  agent without needing Gmail, Pub/Sub, or a real email. Use this to
  verify the full pipeline works end-to-end.

  The simulated email uses IDs prefixed with "sim-" so Gmail action tools
  automatically return mock responses without making real API calls.

URL:
  POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/test/simulate

Request:
  Method  : POST
  Body    : (none)

Response:
  Status       : 200 OK
  Content-Type : application/json

  Body:
  {
    "status": "simulation started",
    "dashboard": "http://127.0.0.1:8000"
  }

  NOTE: The response returns immediately. The agent runs in a background
        thread. Watch the live results at http://127.0.0.1:8000 or by
        connecting to GET /events.

Simulated email content:
  {
    "sender":  "Security Team <security@paypa1-alert.com>",
    "subject": "URGENT: Your account has been suspended",
    "body":    "Phishing email with suspicious URL and .exe attachment",
    "urls":    ["http://paypa1-alert.com/verify?token=abc123"],
    "attachments": [{ "filename": "invoice.pdf.exe", "size_bytes": 512000 }],
    "headers": { "Reply-To": "harvest@scam.ru" }
  }

  Expected agent output:
  - category    : Spam or Phishing
  - risk_score  : 80–100
  - severity    : High or Critical
  - recommendation : High-risk phishing attempt or Mark as spam
  - suggested_reply : (empty — reply is suppressed for high-risk emails)
  - mcp_actions : [{ "action": "move_to_trash", "status": "trashed",
                     "detail": "Mock moved to trash (simulation)" }]

Example (curl):
  curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/test/simulate

Example (PowerShell):
  Invoke-RestMethod -Method POST -Uri http://127.0.0.1:8000/test/simulate

