================================================================================
  DECISION → MCP ACTION MAPPING
================================================================================

  The supervisor agent decides which Gmail tools to call based on its
  analysis. The following are the intended mappings:

  Decision                     → Gmail Actions Taken
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Safe to reply                → generate_reply → send_reply + mark_as_read
  Archive                      → archive_email + mark_as_read
  Mark as spam                 → label_as_spam (SPAM label, removed from INBOX)
  Delete                       → move_to_trash
  Requires manual review       → add_label("Needs Review") + mark_as_unread
  High-risk phishing attempt   → move_to_trash + add_label("Phishing Detected")

  Tool-level guardrails (enforced inside the MCP tools themselves):
  ┌──────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Tool                 │ Requirement                                        │
  ├──────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ move_to_trash        │ analyze_security must have been called first AND   │
  │                      │ risk_score >= AUTO_DELETE_THRESHOLD (default 90)   │
  ├──────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ label_as_spam        │ analyze_security must have been called first AND   │
  │                      │ risk_score >= AUTO_SPAM_THRESHOLD (default 75)     │
  ├──────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ send_reply           │ analyze_security must have been called first AND   │
  │                      │ risk_score < REPLY_RISK_THRESHOLD (default 40) AND │
  │                      │ category NOT in Spam/Newsletter/Promotion/Shopping │
  └──────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  If a tool's guardrail is not satisfied it returns:
    { "status": "refused", "reason": "<explanation>" }
  and no Gmail API call is made. The supervisor agent sees the refusal
  and adjusts its plan accordingly.

  Simulation bypass:
  When message_id or thread_id starts with "sim-" or "test-", every
  Gmail action tool returns a mock success response without calling
  the real Gmail API.

